# AI Summary Feature — Copyright & Licensing Verdict with Web Search

After all research steps complete, Osmium should produce a final **AI-powered summary** that:
1. Checks **master rights** (label/studio ownership)
2. Searches the **studio/label** online to verify if they enforce licensing
3. Gives a clear **YES / NO / UNCLEAR** answer: *"Does this track require a license to use?"*
4. Provides **actionable licensing guidance**

---

## Web Search API Options

The AI summary agent needs to search the web in real-time to look up labels, studios, and licensing policies. Here are the **4 best options**, ranked by recommendation:

| API | Free Tier | Cost After Free | Best For | Node.js SDK |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **🥇 Tavily** | 1,000 credits/mo | $0.008/credit | AI agents & RAG — returns structured, AI-ready results | `@tavily/core` |
| **🥈 Brave Search** | ~1,000 queries/mo (credit-based) | $5/1,000 queries | General web search, independent index | `brave-search` |
| **🥉 SerpAPI** | 250 searches/mo | $25/mo for 1,000 | Google SERP scraping, structured JSON | `serpapi` |
| **Google Custom Search** | 100/day | $5/1,000 queries | ⚠️ **Closed to new customers** — avoid | `googleapis` |

### Recommendation

> [!TIP]
> **Tavily** is the strongest choice because:
> - **1,000 free credits/month** — enough for ~500-1,000 searches
> - **Built for AI agents** — returns clean, structured content ideal for LLM consumption
> - **Official TypeScript SDK** — `@tavily/core` with proper types
> - **Fast** — optimized for real-time AI workflows
>
> **Brave Search** is a solid runner-up if you prefer a more general-purpose search engine with its own independent index.

---

## Proposed Changes

### New Step: AI Summary (Step 9)

The pipeline currently has 8 steps. We add **Step 9: "ai-summary"** that runs after the risk assessment and produces a human-readable copyright/licensing summary.

---

### Types

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///f:/Osmium/src/types/index.ts)

- Add `AISummary` interface with fields: `isCopyrighted`, `requiresLicense`, `masterRightsHolder`, `labelInfo`, `licensingVerdict`, `explanation`, `webSearchSources`
- Add `"ai-summary"` to the [PipelineStepName](file:///f:/Osmium/src/types/index.ts#227-236) union
- Add `aiSummary` field to [CopyrightVerdict](file:///f:/Osmium/src/types/index.ts#178-222)

---

### Web Search Service

#### [NEW] [web-search.ts](file:///f:/Osmium/src/services/web-search.ts)

- Implements a `searchWeb(query: string, apiKey: string): Promise<WebSearchResult[]>` function
- Uses **Tavily** (primary recommendation) or **Brave Search** (alternative) via their SDK
- Searches for label/studio licensing policies, copyright enforcement info
- Returns structured results (title, URL, content snippet)

---

### AI Summary Agent

#### [NEW] [summary-agent.ts](file:///f:/Osmium/src/agents/summary-agent.ts)

- Takes the completed [CopyrightVerdict](file:///f:/Osmium/src/types/index.ts#178-222) + web search results about the label/studio
- Uses OpenRouter LLM to produce a **clear, human-readable summary**:
  - Is the track copyrighted? (YES/NO/UNCLEAR)
  - Does using this track require a license? (YES/NO/DEPENDS)
  - Who holds master rights?
  - What kind of label is it? (major label, indie, self-released, etc.)
  - What are the licensing implications?
  - Actionable next steps for the user

---

### Pipeline

#### [MODIFY] [runner.ts](file:///f:/Osmium/src/pipeline/runner.ts)

- Add **Step 9: "ai-summary"** after the existing risk assessment step
- Performs web searches for:
  - `"{label name}" music licensing policy`
  - `"{label name}" copyright enforcement`
  - `"{label name}" record label type` (major/indie)
- Passes web search results + verdict to the summary agent
- Attaches the `AISummary` to the final [CopyrightVerdict](file:///f:/Osmium/src/types/index.ts#178-222)

---

### CLI Output

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///f:/Osmium/src/index.ts)

- Update step count from `/8` to `/9`
- Add a new **"AI Summary"** section at the end of `displayVerdict()` that shows:
  - A colored banner: 🟢 "NO LICENSE REQUIRED" / 🟡 "LICENSE MAY BE REQUIRED" / 🔴 "LICENSE REQUIRED"
  - The full AI-generated explanation
  - Web sources consulted

---

### Config

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///f:/Osmium/src/config/index.ts)

- Add `webSearch.apiKey` and `webSearch.provider` (`"tavily"` | `"brave"`) to [AppConfig](file:///f:/Osmium/src/types/index.ts#262-280)
- Read from `TAVILY_API_KEY` or `BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY` env variables

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///f:/Osmium/src/types/index.ts)

- Add `webSearch` config type to [AppConfig](file:///f:/Osmium/src/types/index.ts#262-280)

