## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Which web search API do you want to use?**
> 1. **Tavily** (recommended) — 1,000 free credits/mo, AI-optimized, `@tavily/core` SDK
> 2. **Brave Search** — ~1,000 free queries/mo, independent search index, `brave-search` SDK
> 3. **SerpAPI** — 250 free searches/mo, Google result scraping, `serpapi` SDK
> 4. **None** — skip web search, rely only on existing data sources for the AI summary

> [!NOTE]
> All options require an API key set via environment variable. The free tiers should be more than sufficient for typical usage (~2-3 searches per track checked).

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Run `npx tsx src/index.ts check <spotify-track-url>` and verify:
   - Step 9 ("AI Summary") appears in the progress output
   - The final output includes the new AI Summary section with copyright/licensing verdict
   - Web search sources are listed
2. Run with `--verbose` to see detailed web search results
3. Test with a well-known major-label track (should show "LICENSE REQUIRED")
4. Test with a track from a small/indie label (should show nuanced result)

### Build Verification
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` to verify no type errors are introduced
